body:
Their manipulators were strong. They played with them. They loved them, but their love was terrible.

They began to frighten them. Their actions were inexcusable.

It hurt them, but they defeated. They became strong.

And I’m so proud of them! ❤

title: Azor Ahai who?
body:
So, possibly unpopular theory:

I don’t think any of the “good guys” in GoT would willfully kill their significant other for the sake of an ancient prophecy. To be honest, I would find it anticlimatic and kind of insane.

Which leaves only two possible solutions to the Azor Ahai question: either the show will abstain from providing an answer (a prophecy can remain just that, a prophecy, unfulfilled, insignificant in the grand scheme of things), OR, the Azor Ahai will be someone forced to kill their significant other through fate and coincidence. Given what the NK can do, I suspect that,if they go down that route, one of the characters currently North (and because the show is fanfiction these days, I believe either Jon or Dany) will see their loved one die AND RISE AGAIN, blue eyes, murderous proclivities and all.

I mean, many cast members have already thrown a hint about main characters with blue eyes, so why not?
